In honor of Losar, the Tibetan New Year, The Tibetan Gallery & Studio and The Dalai Lama Foundation present a special celebration featuring an art auction and fundraising event. T
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
In honor of Losar, the Tibetan New Year, The Tibetan Gallery & Studio and The Dalai Lama Foundation present a special celebration featuring an art auction and fundraising event. The auction will include a Tibetan thangka and works by Tashi Dhargyal, founder of the Tibetan Gallery & Studio, as well as selected works from The Dalai Lama Foundation’s art exhibition, The Missing Peace: Artists Consider the Dalai Lama. All of the proceeds from the evening will be shared equally between the two organizations. The event will open with a special blessing by local Tibetan monks and there will be a silent auction as well as a live auction featuring art as well as experiential items. Catered hors d’oeuvres with wines by Marimar Estates, Bevan Cellars, MacPhail, La Follette, Hestan Vineyards and nonalcoholic beverages provide by The Kefiry. We will also be sampling some traditional Losar foods. In addition to the auctions, there will be live entertainment featuring Tibetan musicians. Tickets available are $108 and available from Brown Paper Tickets - http://tibetangallery.brownpapertickets.com/

"Sweat Session II":Yoga with Sarah Barnard at BAM
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
If you have been looking for an excuse to check out The Possible at the Berkeley Art Museum, tomorrow is a good opportunity. Weather depending, Sarah's class will either be on Fritz Haeg's rug in the museum around 1:00 or out in the courtyard maybe more around 2:00. Or maybe both. Anything is possible. Bring a mat if you have one but its not required. And if you're not in a yoga mood, the outdoor showers will be open encouraging physical engagement of any sort, so come hike Strawberry Canyon or Tilden in the Berkeley Hills, take a run through campus, play weird made up games in the courtyard, or just enjoy all the performances, workshops, and exhibits going on tomorrow all as parts of The Possible. Museum is open 11-5.
